WorkItem.Description:
It is possible to compile the following function code:

```
private foo(value: number): bool {
       if (value == 0) {
          return true;
       }
}
```

Shouldn't this result in a compilation error saying something like: "not all code paths return a value"?

If the above should be allowed (ex. assuming return value is undefined, which converts to false) then it should be possible not to return anything in a function like:
```
private foo(value: number): bool { }
```

I was unable to find any information for the above in the Language Specification document. My guess is when I give return type other then void a value should always be explicitly returned.
